tp:treatment-sec.p:
HEAD (
Fig. 2D
). Dorsal inter-ocular distance approximately seven times width of one eye. Punctures on frons separated by less than one diameter of each puncture, almost contiguous. Punctures on head disc separated by one diameter of each puncture.

PRONOTUM (
Fig. 3D
). Medial angle projected. Punctures on the disc separated by less than one diameter, almost contiguous. Shiny points on disc irregular and contiguous to punctures.

ABDOMEN (
Fig. 6D
). Width of expansion of the ventrite I, on ventrite III, subequal to distance between clypeal teeth; expansion reaching middle of ventrite IV. Margins of expansion between ventrites II–IV forming an acute angle. Apex of expansion truncate. Basal area of expansion with punctures separated by less than one diameter, almost contiguous.
